    <title>User Profile Card</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="profile-card">
        <h2>John Doe</h2>
        <p>Web Developer at XYZ Company. Loves coding and coffee.</p>
        <button class="button">Contact</button>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

.profile-card {
    width: 300px;
    background-color:rgb(255,255,255);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
}

.profile-card .button {
    background-color: rgb(76, 174, 79);
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    font-size: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 5px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease-in-out;
}

.profile-card .button:hover {
    background-color: rgb(69, 170, 63);
}

***************************** Session-2 CSS*****************************************************
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Introduction Project</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
      
        <nav>
            <a href="#">Home</a>
            <a href="#">Introduction</a>
            <a href="#">Syntax</a>
            <a href="#">Properties</a>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <h1>Introduction to CSS</h1>
        <p>CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is a language used to style and layout web pages. CSS allows you to apply styles to web pages, such as fonts, colors, and spacing, without changing the underlying HTML content.</p>
        <p>Here are some of the benefits of using CSS:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Improved separation of concerns: CSS separates the presentation of a web page from its content, making the code more maintainable.</li>
            <li>Easier to maintain: Changes to the style of a web page can be made in one place (the CSS file) instead of having to modify the HTML code for each page.</li>
            <li>More consistent design: CSS can be used to create a consistent look and feel for a website across all pages.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Basic CSS Syntax</h2>
        <p>A basic CSS rule consists of a selector and a declaration block.</p>
        <pre>
            selector {
                property: value;
            }
        </pre>
        <p>The selector specifies the HTML element(s) that the style rule applies to. The declaration block contains one or more property-value pairs, separated by semicolons. The property specifies the style that you want to change, and the value specifies the new value for that property.</p>

        <h2>Example</h2>
        <p>Let's look at an example of how to use CSS to change the color of all the paragraph elements on a web page.</p>
        <pre>
            p {
                color: red;
            }
        </pre>
        <p>This code will change the color of all the `<p>` elements on the page to red.</p>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 CSS Introduction Project</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>

/* Basic styles */
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  
  h1, h2 {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: rgb(231, 76, 70);
  }
  
  /* Header styles */
  header {
    background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Adjust background color as needed */
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
  }
  
  header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem; /* Adjust font size as needed */
  }
  
  nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-around; /* Adjust spacing as needed */
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem auto; /* Adjust margin as needed */
    background-color: rgb(52, 73, 94);
  }
  
  nav a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #333; /* Adjust text color as needed */
    font-weight: bold; /* Adjust font weight as needed */
  }

  nav a:hover{
    background-color:rgb(44, 62, 80) ;
  }
  
  /* Main content styles */
  main {
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  
  p {
    line-height: 1.5; /* Adjust line height as needed */
  }
  
  pre {
    background-color:rgb(244, 244, 244); /* Adjust background color as needed */
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd; /* Adjust border color as needed */
    overflow-x: auto; /* Enable horizontal scrolling if needed */
  }
  
  /* Footer styles */
  footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    background-color:rgb(52,73,94); /* Adjust background color as needed */
  }



